in</span><span class=3D"mopen">(</span><span class=3D"mord mathnormal">x</s=
pan><span class=3D"mclose">)</span></span></span></span></span> for inputs =
close to but not equal to zero.  The Maclaurin series is used to create a p=
olynomial that matches the values of <span><span class=3D"katex"><span clas=
s=3D"katex-mathml"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><sema=
