<div class=3D"section collapsed" id=3D"section-interval-and-radius-of-conve=
rgence"><div class=3D"section-container">

<p>The <strong>interval of convergence</strong> is the open, closed, or sem=
iclosed range of values of <span><span class=3D"katex"><span class=3D"katex=
-mathml"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mro=
w><mi>x</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">x</annotation=
></semantics></math></span><span class=3D"katex-html" aria-hidden=3D"true">=
<span class=3D"base"><span class=3D"strut" style=3D"height: 0.4306em;"></sp=
an><span class=3D"mord mathnormal">x</span></span></span></span></span> for=
 which the Maclaurin series converges to the value of the function; outside=
 the domain, the Maclaurin series either is undefined or does not relate to=
 the function. The <strong>radius of convergence</strong> is half the lengt=
h of the interval; it is also the radius of the circle in the <a href=3D"ht=
tps://brilliant.org/wiki/complex-plane/" class=3D"wiki_link" title=3D"compl=
ex plane" target=3D"_blank">complex plane</a> within which the series conve=
rges.</p>

<p>Convergence may be determined by a <a href=3D"https://brilliant.org/wiki=
/convergence-tests/" class=3D"wiki_link" title=3D"variety of methods" targe=
t=3D"_blank">variety of methods</a>, but the <a href=3D"https://brilliant.o=
rg/wiki/convergence-ratio-test/" class=3D"wiki_link" title=3D"ratio test" t=
arget=3D"_blank">ratio test</a> tends to provide an immediate value <span><=
span class=3D"katex"><span class=3D"katex-mathml"><math xmlns=3D"http://www=
.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>r</mi></mrow><annotation enc=
oding=3D"application/x-tex">r</annotation></semantics></math></span><span c=
lass=3D"katex-html" aria-hidden=3D"true"><span class=3D"base"><span class=
=3D"strut" style=3D"height: 0.4306em;"></span><span class=3D"mord mathnorma=
l" style=3D"margin-right: 0.0278em;">r</span></span></span></span></span> f=
or the radius of convergence. The interval of convergence may then be deter=
mined by testing the value of the series at the endpoints <span><span class=
=3D"katex"><span class=3D"katex-mathml"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/19=
98/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mo>=E2=88=92</mo><mi>r</mi></mrow><annota=
tion encoding=3D"application/x-tex">-r</annotation></semantics></math></spa=
n><span class=3D"katex-html" aria-hidden=3D"true"><span class=3D"base"><spa=
n class=3D"strut" style=3D"height: 0.6667em; vertical-align: -0.0833em;"></=
span><span class=3D"mord">=E2=88=92</span><span class=3D"mord mathnormal" s=
tyle=3D"margin-right: 0.0278em;">r</span></span></span></span></span> and <=
span><span class=3D"katex"><span class=3D"katex-mathml"><math xmlns=3D"http=
://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>r</mi></mrow><annotati=
on encoding=3D"application/x-tex">r</annotation></semantics></math></span><=
span class=3D"katex-html" aria-hidden=3D"true"><span class=3D"base"><span c=
